The paper discusses the use of Generative Neural Networks (GNNs) to improve the performance of Evolutionary Strategies (ES) algorithms. This topic is closely related to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), neural networks (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and systems and control (cs.SY). Given the focus on optimization and search algorithms, cs.LG and cs.NE are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.AI, cs.CV, and cs.SY.
